index 00000000..e21880dc
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/agent-skills.md
@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@
+# Hive Agent Skills
+
+Hive's core binary is distributed separately from agent skills. The binary must
+not install, update, or remove Claude, Codex, Pi, or other agent-specific skill
+files.
+
+The source for the Hive skills package lives under `skills/hive/` so releases can
+publish it as a separate artifact. Installation is allowed only through a native
+marketplace or plugin flow exposed by the host agent. When a marketplace is not
+available, the installer prompt reports that manual follow-up is required.
+
+Supported marketplace targets for v1 metadata:
+
+- Claude: `skills/hive/marketplaces/claude.yml`
+- Codex: `skills/hive/marketplaces/codex.yml`
+- Pi: `skills/hive/marketplaces/pi.yml`
+
+Each target is declarative. Marketplace-specific automation can be added only
+after the corresponding agent exposes a real install mechanism.
diff --git a/docs/daemon.md b/docs/daemon.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..a90828ea
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/daemon.md
@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@
+# Hive Daemon Service
+
+`hive init` registers a service definition for the host platform:
+
+- Linux: systemd user unit, `hive.service`
+- macOS: launchd plist, `org.hive.daemon.plist`
+
+Registration and autostart are separate. Hive does not silently enable or start
+the service during install.
+
+Manual commands:
+
+```bash
+hive daemon start
+hive daemon status
+hive daemon stop
+```
+
+For package-manager or OS autostart management, inspect the rendered service
+file and enable it explicitly with `systemctl --user enable --now hive.service`
+or the launchd equivalent.
diff --git a/docs/install.md b/docs/install.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..c77eac9d
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/install.md
@@ -0,0 +1,66 @@
+# Install Hive
+
+Hive v1 installation channels consume GitHub Release artifacts. Do not rebuild
+from source in install channels.
+
+- macOS arm64: `brew install <org>/hive/hive`
+- Arch Linux: `hive-bin` from AUR
+- Ubuntu 22.04+ / glibc Linux x86_64 fallback:
+  `curl -fsSL https://github.com/<org>/hive/releases/download/v0.1.0/install.sh | bash`
+- Agent-driven install: paste `prompts/install.md` into a supported agent.
+
+Verify every install with:
+
+```bash
+hive --version
+```
+
+Then initialize each project explicitly:
+
+```bash
+cd /path/to/project
+hive init
+```
+
+Hive uses XDG paths by default:
+
+- Config: `~/.config/hive/config.yml`
+- Data: `~/.local/share/hive/`
+- State: `~/.local/state/hive/`
+- Cache: `~/.cache/hive/`
+
+Project scaffolding lives under `.hive/`; pipeline state lives under
+`.hive-state/`.
+
+## macOS arm64 Homebrew
+
+```bash
+brew install <org>/hive/hive
+hive --version
+hive init
+hive daemon status
+```
+
+Use `hv` if another `hive` executable is earlier on `PATH`.
+
+## Arch AUR
+
+```bash
+yay -S hive-bin
+hive --version
+hive init
+hive daemon status
+```
+
+`hive update` delegates back to the configured AUR helper for `hive-bin`.
+
+## Script Fallback
+
+```bash
+curl -fsSL https://github.com/<org>/hive/releases/download/v0.1.0/install.sh | bash
+hive --version
+hive init
+```
+
+The script writes `~/.config/hive/install_receipt.yml` so `hive update` can
+re-run the release installer later.
diff --git a/docs/release.md b/docs/release.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..aca90e39
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/release.md
@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+# Release Process
+
+Release artifacts are canonical. Homebrew, AUR, script installs, and agent
+prompt installs all consume GitHub Release assets.
+
+1. Tag a semver release such as `v0.1.0`.
+2. Run `.github/workflows/release.yml`.
+3. Confirm artifacts exist:
+   - `hive-v0.1.0-darwin-arm64.tar.gz`
+   - `hive-v0.1.0-linux-x86_64-gnu.tar.gz`
+   - `hive-v0.1.0-checksums.txt`
+4. Run release smoke checks for `hive --version`, `hive init --dry-run` when
+   available, and daemon command help.
+5. Stamp Homebrew and AUR metadata with the artifact SHA256 values.
+6. Complete the tier-1 acceptance checklists under `test/e2e/`.
+
+Do not mark a v1 release ready unless tier-1 acceptance is green or manual
+evidence is attached to the release notes.
