new file mode 100644
index 00000000..316eec94
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/uninstall.md
@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+# Uninstall Hive
+
+`hive uninstall` removes generated service registrations and script-owned
+binaries. It preserves project work by default.
+
+Package-manager installs should use their native owner:
+
+```bash
+brew uninstall <org>/hive/hive
+yay -R hive-bin
+```
+
+Project `.hive/` cleanup is prompted/default-preserved. `~/.local/state/hive/`
+and completed pipeline artifacts are preserved, including with `--purge`.
+
+Hive skills are separate marketplace packages. Remove skills through the agent
+marketplace that installed them.
