@@ -0,0 +1,71 @@
+---
+title: Packaging
+type: release
+source: packaging/, hive.gemspec, .github/workflows/release.yml
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [packaging, release, install]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: Hive release artifacts are semver-tagged GitHub Release tarballs built from `packaging/build/build_release.rb`. The contract names tier-1 assets as `hive-vX.Y.Z-<target>.tar.gz`, writes `.sha256` files plus a combined checksums file, and embeds version/commit/build-time/target metadata beside the packaged `hive` executable.
+
+## Artifact Contract
+
+The shared contract lives in `Hive::Packaging::BuildRelease`:
+
+- Semver tags must match `vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH` with optional prerelease/build metadata.
+- Tier-1 targets are `darwin-arm64` and `linux-x86_64-gnu`.
+- The canonical names are `hive-v0.1.0-darwin-arm64.tar.gz`, `hive-v0.1.0-linux-x86_64-gnu.tar.gz`, and `hive-v0.1.0-checksums.txt`.
+- Each tarball unpacks an executable named `hive` and a JSON manifest with the `hive-release-artifact` schema.
+
+The release workflow uses Tebako `press` in bundle mode so the binary includes Ruby and gem dependencies. During packaging it stamps `lib/hive/build_metadata.rb` with the plain semver version, commit, build time, and target before running Tebako, then restores the source file. Artifact names and manifests keep the `vX.Y.Z` tag contract, while `Hive::VERSION` stays gemspec-safe (`X.Y.Z`). The publish job generates the combined `hive-vX.Y.Z-checksums.txt` after both platform artifacts are downloaded so `install.sh` has one canonical manifest. Install channels consume these release artifacts instead of rebuilding from source. See [[modules/config]] for the XDG runtime paths that packaged installs use.
+
+## Homebrew
+
+`packaging/homebrew/Formula/hive.rb` is the tap formula for macOS arm64. It downloads `hive-vX.Y.Z-darwin-arm64.tar.gz`, verifies SHA256, installs `hive`, and adds an `hv` symlink for command-name conflicts. The formula intentionally has no `depends_on "ruby"` because the release artifact is self-contained.
+
+`packaging/homebrew/update_formula.rb` renders the formula from release metadata. The checked-in formula keeps a placeholder checksum until the release workflow or maintainer stamps the real SHA from GitHub Releases.
+
+## Arch AUR
+
+`packaging/aur/hive-bin/PKGBUILD` is the binary Arch package. It downloads `hive-vX.Y.Z-linux-x86_64-gnu.tar.gz`, verifies SHA256, installs `/usr/bin/hive`, and adds `/usr/bin/hv`. The package is named `hive-bin`, provides `hive`, conflicts with a source-built `hive`, and does not depend on Ruby.
+
+`packaging/aur/update_pkgbuild.rb` renders both `PKGBUILD` and `.SRCINFO` from release metadata. `PKGBUILD` can keep `v${pkgver}` shell expansion, but `.SRCINFO` is rendered with the expanded `vX.Y.Z` URL to match `makepkg --printsrcinfo`. The checked-in files keep placeholder checksums until release time.
+
+## Script Installer
+
+`install.sh` is the fallback `curl | bash` installer. It detects tier-1 platforms, prefers Homebrew on macOS and AUR helpers on Arch unless `HIVE_INSTALL_PREFER_NATIVE=0`, downloads GitHub Release artifacts for direct installs, verifies SHA256, installs into `~/.local/bin`, creates XDG directories, and writes `~/.config/hive/install_receipt.yml`.
+
+The script chooses `hv` when an unrelated `hive` executable is already first on `PATH`. It prints actionable hints for missing dependencies and does not install third-party tools.
+
+## Init and Service Registration
+
+`hive init` now also creates a project-facing `.hive/` scaffold from `templates/project/.hive/`. The existing `.hive-state/` worktree remains the pipeline state store; `.hive/` is for versioned project-local defaults.
+
+Service templates live under `templates/service/`. `Hive::Service::SystemdUser` renders `hive.service`; `Hive::Service::Launchd` renders `org.hive.daemon.plist`. `hive init` registers the service definition but does not enable autostart implicitly. The init prompt has a separate default-no `daemon_autostart` question; only an explicit yes calls `enable_and_start`, and launchd registration renders `RunAtLoad` false until that consent is given.
+
+## Lifecycle Commands
+
+`Hive::InstallReceipt` reads `~/.config/hive/install_receipt.yml` for script installs. `hive update` delegates to the native owner: Homebrew runs `brew upgrade <org>/hive/hive`, AUR runs the configured helper against `hive-bin`, and script installs re-run the release `install.sh`. Unknown install channels raise `Hive::Error` after printing manual reinstall guidance so wrapper agents see a non-zero exit.
+
+`hive uninstall` removes service registrations and script-owned binaries, but package-manager installs are told to use their native uninstall command. Project `.hive/` cleanup is preserved by default. `--purge` expresses cleanup intent, then `.hive/` removal still requires either a TTY yes at the project-cleanup prompt or `--yes` for non-interactive confirmation. `~/.local/state/hive` work artifacts are preserved.
+
+## Agent Prompt and Skills Package
+
+`prompts/install.md` is the published agent-installer prompt. It requires OS/channel detection, `hive --version` verification before `hive init`, an explicit prompt before project setup, and marketplace-only skills installation.
+
+The skills package source lives under `skills/hive/` but is a separate distribution artifact. The core binary must not write agent directories; unsupported marketplace targets degrade to manual follow-up.
+
+## Operator Documentation and Acceptance
+
+Operator docs live in `docs/install.md`, `docs/update.md`, `docs/uninstall.md`, `docs/daemon.md`, and `docs/release.md`. Tier-1 acceptance checklists live under `test/e2e/*acceptance.md`; `.github/workflows/e2e-install.yml` runs the Ubuntu script-installer dry run and docs contract tests.
+
+## Tests
+
+`test/release/artifact_contract_test.rb` validates semver gating, target rejection, deterministic names, manifest metadata, and SHA256 file format. `test/packaging/homebrew_formula_test.rb` validates the tap formula contract. `test/packaging/aur_pkgbuild_test.rb` validates the AUR metadata contract. `test/install/install_sh_test.rb` validates script-installer platform detection, unsupported-platform behavior, command conflict handling, and receipt writing. The default `rake test` task includes `test/release`, `test/packaging`, and `test/install`.
+
+## Backlinks
+
+- [[architecture]]
+- [[dependencies]]
+- [[testing]]
